  "texts": [
    "Particle size plays a crucial role, particularly with RHA and WGP, where finer particles are more effective at enhancing concrete properties. 5.",
    "Fineness, the measure of particle size, significantly influences the performance of cementitious materials, affecting workability, setting time, strength, and hydration rate.",
    "High-fineness materials like (SF), (MK), and (RHA) enhance concrete properties through improved pore-filling and rapid pozzolanic activity, while lower-fineness materials like (ESP) and (FA) primarily act as fillers or contribute to gradual strength improvement.",
    "Strategies such as pre-grinding, blending with reactive materials, and optimizing mix designs can enhance the performance of low-fineness materials. 6.",
    "SCMs offer several advantages, including lower CO 2 emissions, improved durability, and cost savings."
